### What problem does this feature solve?
Currently when using nameSpaced modules, one can alias the method if the name is unique. My issue is that I often have the same method names in each module - ie: `actions: { update() { ... } }`.

If I were to map them, I either have to explicitly use the full namespace to describe the alias ie: `this['user/update']() && this['status/update]()`, otherwise one of them will be superseded at runtime.

By allowing the module alias feature to be declared within an array,  then multiple methods can be duly created that share the same method names yet be written explicitly unique as when needed within a component, because currently using the map helper only allows for one alias at a time.
Ultimately it will allow this: 
```
this.addTodo()
this.removeTodo()
this.addUser()
this.removeUser()
// from the following declaration
methods: {
    ...mapMutations('todos', [{ addTodo: 'add' }, { removeTodo: 'destroy' }],
    ...mapMutations('users', [{ addUser: 'add' }, { removeUser: 'destroy' }]
}
```

### What does the proposed API look like?
```
// currently only this works
methods: {
    ...mapActions('todos', { addTodo: 'increment' }) // map `this.addTodo()` to `this.$store.commit('increment')`
}
// proposed feature :
methods: {
    ...mapActions('todos', [{ addTodo: 'increment' }]) // wrap within array so that multiple module methods can be aliased cleanly
}
```

